definition.value: A (4-deoxygluc-4-enosyluronic acid)-(1->3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine sulfate in which the 4-deoxygluc-4-enosyluronic acid component has beta-D configuration.
A beta-D-glucoside having a beta-D-apiosyl residue at the 2-position and a 5,4'-dihydroxyflavon-7-yl moiety at the anomeric position.
A UDP-sugar having D-apiose as the sugar portion.
An aminouracil that is D-ribitol in which the hydroxy group at position 1 is substituted by the 6-amino group of 5,6-diaminouracil. Early intermediate in bacterial riboflavin synthesis.
